<!-- Assess & Convert -->

### Overview{.c-heading-4}

By using SQL Server Migration Assistant (SSMA) for DB2, you can review database objects and data, assess databases for migration, migrate DB2 database objects to Azure SQL Database, and then migrate data to Azure SQL Database.

**Note**: For more information about SSMA, see the article [SQL Server Migration Assistant for DB2 (DB2ToSQL)]( https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/ssma/db2/sql-server-migration-assistant-for-db2-db2tosql).

### Process

To use SSMA for DB2 to create an assessment, perform the following steps.

1.Download SSMA from the Microsoft Download Center [here]( https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=54254), and then install it.

_SSMA is now ready for use._

2.Assess the source database and discover conversion rate and effort to resolve issues. For more information about SSMA for DB2 Assessments, see the article [Assessing DB2 Schemas for Conversion (DB2ToSQL)](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/ssma/db2/assessing-db2-schemas-for-conversion-db2tosql).

_This will generate an Assessment Report which shows the results of the conversion of database objects to Transact-SQL syntax, and can also help you estimate the complexity and cost of your migration projects._

3.Converting DB2 Schemas. For more information about SSMA for DB2 Conversion, see the article [Converting DB2 Schemas (DB2ToSQL)](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/ssma/db2/converting-db2-schemas-db2tosql).

_When the schema conversion is complete, you are ready to move on to the Migration phase._

**Note**: For complete step-by-step guidance on installing and using SSMA for DB2, see the following resources:

